                    "company": "Joris Kleverlaan Consultancy",
                    "description": "Joris Kleverlaan Consultancy started out as a subsidy consultancy company. From the start onwards, I took opportunity to sharpen my skills as a linguist and a communication professional. Writing, editing, and translating, lecturing, and at the same time organizing and presenting events for the August Willemsen Foundation; it has turned me into a multi-tasking renaissance man on language and communication.\n\nCommissions of which I am truly proud:\n2016-2017 Lecturer Creative Business faculty of the Utrecht University of Applied Sciences.\n\nAs Senior Editor for BNN-Vara, I am involved in the making of Per Seconde Wijzer, a quiz that has been running for decades. My involvement include editing questions, writing introductory short stories, and both linguistic and content editing during recordings.\n\nFranjo Films from Amsterdam: involved as editor, translator, and advisor in the making of an upcoming documentary on the work and life of August Willemsen, translator from Portuguese, and writer. Succesful research trips to Brasil were completed in March and April of 2017.\n\nAlso:\n- N'GOL\u00c1 Biennial of Arts and Culture in S\u00e3o Tom\u00e9 e Pr\u00edncipe. Translation of exhibition texts, websites, and catalogue, from English to Portuguese. In close cooperation with Shanti Luz Communicatie.\n- Teatro Munganga; 30 years. Editing the book of the Dutch-Brazilian theater group.\n- Bureau voor Lokale Zaken. Advisory position for this digital platform for local research journalism\n- Terwel BV; Matchmaking between Dutch and foreign business partners, drafting of business proposals, subsidy applications.\n- EP-Nuffic, writing, editing course material 'International education for project officers'\n- August Willemsen Foundation: initiating, editing, and presenting cultural events\n- translating Dutch-Portuguese Hermitage Museum, Financieel Dagblad\n- Krullen restauratie; projectmatig en taalkundig (Portugees) advies\n- Rapucation Foundation; translation  English-Portuguese",
