                    "company": "Stichting August Willemsen",
                    "description": "The August Willemsen Foundation supports, stimulates and strengthens the cultural ties between Portugese and Dutch speaking countries, with the focus on the literary component. We do this by organizing events, exchanges, and by being ambassadors of language.\n\nAugust Willemsen (1936-2007) was a great translator from Portugese to Dutch, who introduced writers like Pessoa, Guimaraes Rosa, and many others to Dutch readers. Apart from his translations, he published a number of publications under his own name: diaries, letter books, and essays. He inspires us to keep the Portugese language alive among Duch speakers, and to continue stimulating the exchange between these two particular languages in all their beauty.",
